post_text: Congratulations to our football team on their successful Indian Gridiron Classic golf tourney yesterday!
shared_text:
Brent Bauer is with Jacoby Bauer and 3 others at Crandall Creek Golf Club.
June 28 at 9:09 AM ¬∑ Ogallala, NE ¬∑

Indian Gridiron Classic was an incredible success!! We broke records in terms of teams, sponsorships, and donations. Thank you so much to the Ogallala community for the great support!

Crandall Creek Golf Club did a great job hosting almost 200 golfers and volunteers throughout the day! Course looked great and everyone commented on what a great time they had.
Loved seeing the family golf teams out enjoying the day along with many current and former Indian Football Players!
A great day celebrating Indian Football!

Thank you to everyone that made yesterday happen!!

2021 Indian Gridiron Classic-
June 26th
Crandall Creek Golf Club.

Come cheer on the Indians in their home opener Aug 26th vs. Broken Bow @ 6:00 P.M.

#PrairiePlaymakers
#AllFor1
#winEVERYTHING
#Family
*(If anyone has any additional photos please share!)

March 25, 2020 update from Nebraska Schools Activities Association:

All NSAA activity practices and competitions are suspended through May 1. These suspensions may be extended should the conditions warrant.

Member schools and student-participants are expected to adhere to the NSAA Constitution & Bylaws and activity manuals during this time.

The NSAA encourages all member schools to follow CDC, local, state and federal health department recommendations.

As more information becomes available, official updates will be posted on the NSAA website and the NSAA social media platforms.

The official press release:

2:00 pm Press Release:NSAA Announces State Boys Basketball Championship Plans

Lincoln, NE ‚Äì March 11, 2020 ‚Äì Based on the recommendations made by the Mayor‚Äôs Office of the City of Lincoln, Lincoln-Lancaster County Health Department and the Nebraska Department of Education, the 2020 NSAA Boys State Basketball Championships will proceed as scheduled, but fan attendance will be limited. The tournament venues and game times remain the same.

Attendance will be limited to the varsity players, coaches, team support personnel (athletic trainers and student managers) and school administrators of the qualifying schools and their immediate families.

Anyone not on the approved list who previously purchased a ticket will not be allowed entry. Passes will not be honored including NCA Gold Card, NSAA Courtesy Passes and Lifetime passes. This measure is to protect the health and safety of the student athletes, their families and the public at large.
